Environment Variables

The system uses environment variables for configuration. A template file .env.template is version-controlled, while actual .env files are never committed.

.env.template (version controlled):
# FMP API Configuration
FMP_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
FMP_API_URL=https://financialmodelingprep.com/api/v3
FMP_API_DELAY_SECONDS=0.2

# PostgreSQL Database
PGHOST=your_db_host
PGPORT=5432
PGDATABASE=market_data
PGUSER=your_username
PGPASSWORD=your_password

# Application Settings
MARKET_TZ=America/New_York
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
LOG_DIR=./logs

# Data Collection Settings
SYMBOLS=AAPL,MSFT,GOOGL,AMZN
COLLECTION_INTERVAL_MINUTES=60
WINDOW_OVERLAP_MINUTES=5

# Deployment configuration
RUN_AS_USER=myuser
CRON_TIME=*/15 * * * *  # Every 15 minutes